cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the efficient computation of functions in a wireless sensor network modeled as a set of coupled Gaussian multiple-access channels. Information theory concepts such as channel capacity and interference are used in the analysis and design of the proposed computation scheme. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a wireless sensor network and its communication and computation aspects. The proposed scheme involves data pre- and post-processing strategies and a nested lattice code, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the computation of functions in a sensor network, which can be seen as a control problem. The proposed scheme involves designing a suitable code to protect the sensor readings against channel noise, which is a control-related task. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the computation of functions of sensor readings, which can be seen as a multimedia processing task. The proposed scheme involves pre- and post-processing of data, which is relevant to multimedia processing. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper deals with the computation of functions of sensor readings, which can be seen as a machine learning task. The proposed scheme involves designing a suitable code to protect the sensor readings against channel noise, which is relevant to machine learning.
